==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thunderstrike
<hw>Thun"der*strike`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Thunderstruck</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Thunderstruck</conjf>, <conjf>-strucken</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Thunderstriking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To strike,
blast, or injure by, or as by, lightning.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To astonish, or strike dumb, as with something
terrible; -- rarely used except in the past participle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>drove before him, <qex>thunderstruck</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thunderworm</ent>⟦br⟧
